Nevertheless, this verb is frequently used to convey a sense of transporting the verbal object between locations and in a particular direction; the sense of motion may be explicitly supplied by a verbal associated motion suffix such as <-kwaa> ‘go and do’, or it may be conveyed by discourse context; likewise, directional information may be conveyed either by discourse context or by an overt postpositional or adverbial adjunct.
